<div class="artwrap">
  <article class="article reveal">
    <h2>What CNO Stands For</h2>
    <p>CNO stands for Charlie and Nancy Overfield. They opened the business in Clarkston in February 1970, building pole barns for local farms and property owners. The name stuck, and it's still on the trucks today.</p>
    <p>Ownership has changed hands since then. CNO Pole Barns is family owned and operated, and today the business is run by owner Zosim Serban. Customers who leave reviews also mention Ian, who project-manages jobs alongside him. Three crews handle the actual building, and the company carries an A+ rating with the Better Business Bureau.</p>

    <figure class="inline-img riv">
      <img src="/images/team/zosim-serban-2.jpg" alt="Portrait of Zosim Serban, owner of CNO Pole Barns" width="1424" height="1440" loading="lazy">
      <figcaption>Zosim Serban, owner of CNO Pole Barns.</figcaption>
    </figure>

    <h2>How We Work</h2>
    <p>Reviews on Google keep mentioning the same things: Zosim answers the phone, the schedule holds up, and the crew doesn't leave a mess behind. That's not an accident. Every job gets a direct line to the owner instead of a call center, and a contract with numbers that don't move once the work starts.</p>

    <blockquote>
      <p>"Zosim was on top of the project from start to finish and always available to review any questions that came up... After foundation and blocks were in place, the general structure was up in one day, the roof shingled the next morning... There were no surprises concerning financials."</p>
      <p>- Reimund B., 24'x30' garage, Google review</p>
    </blockquote>

    <blockquote>
      <p>"We had some issues being in the city with permits but Zosim was always on top of any problem that arose. Communication was phenomenal. I highly recommend this company."</p>
      <p>- Heather B., garage rebuild after a fire, Google review</p>
    </blockquote>

    <p>The crews clean up when a job's done, too. It's a small thing that shows up in almost every review we get.</p>

